, `/mcp/oauth` | Modern JSON-RPC MCP over HTTP POST. GET returns a lightweight SSE stream for compatibility checks. |\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-json-rpc-runtime.md:1:# MCP JSON-RPC Runtime\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-json-rpc-runtime.md:4:Remote MCP routes implement initialize, initialized notification, tools/list, tools/call, strict auth aliases, and JSON-RPC error semantics.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-json-rpc-runtime.md:6:The reusable JSON-RPC method handling should live behind the `@minasoft/mcp-runtime` package boundary described in `../design-docs/mcp-runtime-library-architecture.md`. MCP Mock Server remains responsible for auth, CORS, SSE route hosting, endpoint matching, fixture persistence, and audit evidence, but it should not keep a second app-local implementation of reusable MCP protocol behavior.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-json-rpc-runtime.md:24:- The server supports JSON-RPC over Streamable HTTP `POST`, lightweight Streamable HTTP `GET` SSE open events, and legacy SSE compatibility aliases at `/sse`, `/sse/none`, `/sse/basic`, and `/sse/oauth`.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-json-rpc-runtime.md:25:- Legacy SSE aliases open a live `text/event-stream`, emit an `endpoint` event for the matching message POST URL, process JSON-RPC messages through the same MCP runtime as Streamable HTTP, and send JSON-RPC responses back over the stream as `message` events.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-json-rpc-runtime.md:27:- MCP `POST` responses include the server protocol version header. Requests that provide an unsupported `MCP-Protocol-Version` header return HTTP `400` with a JSON-RPC invalid-request error; requests without that header remain accepted for compatibility with simple curl/Postman probes.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-json-rpc-runtime.md:31:- `initialize` returns protocol version `2025-06-18` when requested, otherwise the newest MVP-supported version from `2025-06-18` and `2025-03-26`.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-json-rpc-runtime.md:32:- `initialize` advertises `tools: { listChanged: false }`, `resources: { subscribe: true, listChanged: true }`, `prompts: { listChanged: true }`, and `completions: {}` when the runtime handlers are available; logging, sampling, durable session, and resumability capabilities are not claimed.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-json-rpc-runtime.md:34:- `notifications/initialized` is accepted as a JSON-RPC notification with HTTP `202` and no response body.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-json-rpc-runtime.md:38:- `tools/call` for valid OAuth Bearer callers executes permitted endpoint tools and returns HTTP `403` with JSON-RPC error data when the token is valid but does not grant the requested endpoint.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-json-rpc-runtime.md:39:- If no exact response case matches the supplied arguments, the configured default response case is returned. Unknown tools, disabled tools, malformed `tools/call` params, and endpoint argument validation failures return JSON-RPC `-32602` envelopes with HTTP `200`.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-json-rpc-runtime.md:41:- Response-case tool errors return MCP `tools/call` results with `isError: true`; endpoint-level or response-case protocol errors return JSON-RPC `-32000` errors with `protocol_error` data.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-json-rpc-runtime.md:42:- Unsupported JSON-RPC methods return `-32601` with HTTP `200`.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-json-rpc-runtime.md:48:- JSON-RPC parsing/formatting\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-json-rpc-runtime.md:52:- Call initialize, list tools, call a configured tool, and observe route-specific auth behavior\ndocs/references/prd-analysis.md:7:- Public remote MCP mock server with a web UI, MCP JSON-RPC routes, REST mock routes, Basic Auth, and mock OAuth bearer auth.\ndocs/references/prd-analysis.md:16:- MCP JSON-RPC runtime for `initialize`, `notifications/initialized`, `tools/list`, and `tools/call`.\ndocs/references/prd-analysis.md:27:- MCP JSON-RPC response formatting should be contract-tested separately from endpoint matching.\ndocs/PRODUCT_SENSE.md:30:- initialize no-auth MCP clients, list enabled tools, and execute exact-match tool calls\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:22:- `initialize` advertises:\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:34:- Resource-not-found errors use JSON-RPC `-32002`; invalid params use `-32602`; unsupported methods continue to use `-32601`.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:50:- Unit tests cover validators, rendering, completion matching, JSON-RPC envelopes, permission filters, and error mapping.\ndocs/product-specs/rest-mock-api.md:13:- `GET /rest/tools` returns simple JSON, not an MCP JSON-RPC envelope:\ndocs/product-specs/rest-mock-api.md:21:- Successful REST calls return the configured mock response body directly with the configured status code, not a JSON-RPC envelope.\ndocs/RELIABILITY.md:13:- resource and prompt runtime responses must use the same JSON-RPC adapter and auth precedence as tools so full MCP feature coverage does not create a second protocol path\ndocs/RELIABILITY.md:30:- The first runtime slice is stateless: `initialize` does not create an MCP session, `notifications/initialized` returns `202` with no body, and unsupported SSE/session methods return `405` with `Allow: POST`.\ndocs/RELIABILITY.md:32:- `tools/call` in no-auth mode must call the shared endpoint matcher by endpoint name. Unknown or disabled tools and argument validation failures return JSON-RPC `-32602`; unsupported JSON-RPC methods return `-32601`; no exact response-case match falls back to the configured default case.\ndocs/QUALITY_SCORE.md:33:- treat MCP JSON-RPC response shapes as contract tests\ndocs/GETTING_STARTED.md:104:- MCP initialize/list/call/protocol guard\ndocs/GETTING_STARTED.md:130:The page checks `initialize`, one selected MCP method preset, response header evidence, and unsupported protocol-version behavior.\ndocs/product-specs/index.md:11:| `mcp-json-rpc-runtime.md` | confirmed | MCP JSON-RPC Runtime |\ndocs/product-specs/failure-simulation-and-audit.md:16:- Response-case forced errors 